{
  "doc_id": "45215",
  "text": "Complex event processing detects complex events based on a set/sequence of occurrences of primitive events by monitoring the event flow continuously. Etzion and Niblett introduced the concept, architecture, and methods of complex event processing in their book [CITATION_1] . Event processing agent (EPA) is a component that applies some rules to generate complex events as output based on a set of input events. Event processing network (EPN) is a network of a collection of EPAs, event producers, and event consumers linked by channels. The network in EPN is used to describe the event processing flow execution. Luckham first introduced the event processing network in the field of modeling [CITATION_2] .",
